description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applications are invited for 1 whole-time Locum Subspecialist Consultant Gynaecological Oncology Surgeon. In a University Hospitals of Leicester Gynaecological Cancer Centre for 12 months &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is a locum post arising from a colleague moving into an academic post and has Weekly operating sessions&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants must be able to demonstrate tertiary hospital level skills, team working and the ability to develop and/or contribute to sub-speciality training programmes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants must already be on the GMC specialist register, have Gynaecological Oncology sub specialist accreditation, and be proficient in Gynaecological Oncological minimally invasive surgery.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;As this post is regulated by the Protection of Children Act 1999, The Criminal Justice Courts Act 2000 and / or the Care Standards Act 2000 an enhanced disclosure by the Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) will be undertaken.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful appointee will be expected to participate in undergraduate and postgraduate teaching and clinical audit. They will be required to undertake management duties and work in a multidisciplinary team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The University Hospitals of Leicester NHS Trust consists of three acute teaching hospitals serving the population of Leicestershire. It is fully committed to Continuing Medical Education for consultants.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameQuentin DaviesJob titleGynaecology Oncology lead consultantEmail addressquentin.davies@uhl-tr.nhs.ukTelephone number0116 258 4832Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information and for an informal discussion, please contact Quentin Davies cancer lead clinician 0116 258 4832.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications received after this date will not be considered&lt;/p&gt;
